name: railway track construction | railway track | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/6715/documentation

Based on 'railway track construction, CH 2000'. All data is referred to meter*year. Life time of the rail track infrastructure is assumed to be 100 yrs. Inventory for a conventional gravel track bedding. Expenditures due to tunnel construction and bridge construction have been taken into account, according to the share of tunnels and bridges in the Swiss rail network. All data is referred to a two way track. Allocation between goods and passenger transport is not yet applied. For the maintenance and land use data, the inventory represents a conventional gravel track bedding. Expenditures due to tunnel construction and bridge construction have been taken into account, according to the share of tunnels and bridges in the Swiss rail network. Railway track disposal is included as well.

Service starts with the material consumption due to the track bedding, substructure and catenary system. Service for the maintenance and land use starts with the electricty consumption.

The inventory includes the construction of the rail track (track bedding, substructures, catenary system) as well as the construction of tunnels and bridges. Further components of rail track infrastructure, such as signalling infrastructure, train overtaking stations, sound insulation walls and buildings (stations, service garages) are not included in this study. Also land use is not considered, but accounted for in the maintenance and operation, railway track. For the maintenance and land use, the inventory includes the energy consumption required for the operation of the rail track as well as the operation of tunnels. The use and emissions to soil of herbicides (weed control) and lubricates (point maintenance) are taken into account. Also land transformation and occupation are accounted for. Disposal is included.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/421:Construction of roads and railways/4210:Construction of roads and railways

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Rail length is based on current statistical data (2000). The material consumption represents a situation in the early 1990ties and a recent high speed track in Germany
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Extrapolated from 'railway track construction, CH 2000'. Data refers to average conditions in Switzerland and a specific conditions in Germany
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Data represents current technologies;References:;;SBB (2002) Umweltbericht 2000/2001. SBB, Bahnumweltzentrum, Bern, Online-Version under: www.sbb.ch/umwelt.;von Rozycki C., Koeser H. and Schwarz H. (2003) Ecology Profile of the German High-speed Rail Passenger Transport System, ICE. In: International Journal of Life Cycle Assessment, 8(2), pp. 83-91.;Oggier (2002) Entsorgung von Gleisaushub. pdf from http://www.sbb.ch/gs/pdf/umwelt_gleisaushub.pdf.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: none This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
